ome help from the\n--\nDocumentation/core-api/dma-api-howto.rst-95-The following API will work of course even on platforms where no such\nDocumentation/core-api/dma-api-howto.rst-96-hardware exists.\nDocumentation/core-api/dma-api-howto.rst-97-\nDocumentation/core-api/dma-api-howto.rst-98-Note that the DMA API works with any bus independent of the underlying\nDocumentation/core-api/dma-api-howto.rst-99-microprocessor architecture. You should use the DMA API rather than the\nDocumentation/core-api/dma-api-howto.rst:100:bus-specific DMA API, i.e., use the dma_map_*() interfaces rather than the\nDocumentation/core-api/dma-api-howto.rst-101-pci_map_*() interfaces.\nDocumentation/core-api/dma-api-howto.rst-102-\nDocumentation/core-api/dma-api-howto.rst-103-First of all, you should make sure::\nDocumentation/core-api/dma-api-howto.rst-104-\nDocumentation/core-api/dma-api-howto.rst-105-\t#include <linux/dma-mapping.h>\n--\nDocumentation/core-api/dma-api-howto.rst-575-\tstruct device *dev = &my_dev->dev;\nDocumentation/core-api/dma-api-howto.rst-576-\tdma_addr_t dma_handle;\nDocumentation/core-api/dma-api-howto.rst-577-\tvoid *addr = buffer->ptr;\nDocumentation/core-api/dma-api-howto.rst-578-\tsize_t size = buffer->len;\nDocumentation/core-api/dma-api-howto.rst-579-\nDocumentation/core-api/dma-api-howto.rst:580:\tdma_handle = dma_map_single(dev, addr, size, direction);\nDocumentation/core-api/dma-api-howto.rst:581:\tif (dma_mapping_error(dev, dma_handle)) {\nDocumentation/core-api/dma-api-howto.rst-582-\t\t/*\nDocumentation/core-api/dma-api-howto.rst-583-\t\t * reduce current DMA mapping usage,\nDocumentation/core-api/dma-api-howto.rst-584-\t\t * delay and try again later or\nDocumentation/core-api/dma-api-howto.rst-585-\t\t * reset driver.\nDocumentation/core-api/dma-api-howto.rst-586-\t\t */\n--\nDocumentation/core-api/dma-api-howto.rst-589-\nDocumentation/core-api/dma-api-howto.rst-590-and to unmap it::\nDocumentation/core-api/dma-api-howto.rst-591-\nDocumentation/core-a